Perfect! Now I can see the issue clearly. In the `nextTextValue()` method, when processing `XML_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE`:

```java
case XmlTokenStream.XML_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE:
    _currText = _xmlTokens.getText();
    _currToken = JsonToken.VALUE_STRING;
    break;
```

The code properly sets `_currText` to the attribute value and `_currToken` to `JsonToken.VALUE_STRING`, but then it breaks out of the switch statement and falls through to the end of the method where it returns `null`.

This is incorrect. When we have a `XML_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE`, we should return the text value that was just captured in `_currText`, similar to how `XML_TEXT` case does with `return _currText;`.

